<p>What is the syntax for passing subroutine names as arguments? Schematically:</p>  <pre><code>  .   . call action ( mySubX ( argA, argB ) )   .   .  subroutine action ( whichSub ( argA, argB ) )   ... call subroutine whichSub ( argA, argB )   ... end subroutine action </code></pre>  <p>The goal is to have <code>call subroutine whichSub ( argA, argB )</code> act as <code>call subroutine mySubX ( argA, argB )</code>.  My preference is to avoid avoid passing a switch parameter and then use SELECT CASE.</p>